<Docs title="Specline — the CLI & MCP server">
  <div class="doc-kicker">Documentation</div>
  <h1>The CLI &amp; MCP server</h1>
  <p class="doc-lead">
    The Specline CLI checks your repo. It reads your markdown, your YAML, your folder structure — never
    your code, never a model, never the network — and answers one question the same way
    every time: <em>does this repo have the right shape?</em> Same input, same answer, every
    run.
  </p>
  <p>One engine, one output contract. It runs three ways:</p>
  <div class="doc-cards">
    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/setup"><div class="dc-t">Getting started →</div><div class="dc-d">Set up a new repo, or convert an existing one's docs to Specline.</div></a>
    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/install"><div class="dc-t">Install →</div><div class="dc-d">Get the <code>specline</code> command on your machine. Node 22+, no build step.</div></a>
    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/cli"><div class="dc-t">CLI →</div><div class="dc-d"><code>specline check</code>, <code>rules</code>, <code>spec</code> — flags, modes, exit codes.</div></a>
    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/mcp"><div class="dc-t">MCP server →</div><div class="dc-d">Wire Specline in as a tool an agent calls while it plans with you.</div></a>
    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/rules"><div class="dc-t">Rule catalog →</div><div class="dc-d">Every <code>rule_id</code>, its severity, scope, tier, and downgradable flag.</div></a>
    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/agent"><div class="dc-t">Agent setup →</div><div class="dc-d">The <code>CLAUDE.md</code> brief that makes an agent aware of Specline.</div></a>
    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/orchestrator"><div class="dc-t">The orchestrator →</div><div class="dc-d">The pluggable runner that drives a ratified spec autonomously — Specline defines the contract, not the runner.</div></a>
    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/why"><div class="dc-t">Why now →</div><div class="dc-d">Why Specline helps <em>more</em> as models get stronger.</div></a>
    <a class="doc-card" href="/spec.md"><div class="dc-t">Raw canon ↗</div><div class="dc-d">The full methodology as markdown — what Specline enforces, for your agents.</div></a>
  </div>
  <div class="callout"><span class="ci">▲</span><p>Specline checks the shape, nothing more. It never judges meaning — sizing, tense, whether the spec is <em>right</em>. That stays yours, at the two gates.</p></div>
</Docs>
